The paper deals with the stability of a Kalman filter in a networking setting with multiple sensors, which suggests that it falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the numerical computation of stability conditions, which could be related to information theory (cs.IT). The use of a sensor scheduling protocol over a lossy network suggests that the paper could also be related to networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also mentions the generalization of existing results, which could be related to mathematics (cs.MA) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
